The structure detection logic compares each 4H candle's high and low against the previous one to identify lower lows and lower closes (bearish) or higher highs and higher closes (bullish). When these conditions are met, the new structure level gets set to the current candle's low or high, and the outside return values are pulled from two candles back to capture the broader context.

For the violations, the code checks if price spikes through a prior level but fails to close beyond it—bearish violations look for highs exceeding the outside return high while closes stay below it, and bullish violations check for lows dropping below the outside return low with closes remaining above. The zone boundaries get defined based on which direction the violation occurred.

